I just put up these 10 watercolors for sale, if you'd like to pick one up ( or anything else on my store ) you'll be doing me a solid and helping me take care of my girl. Thanks for hearing me out. I'll be back soon! ❤️❤️❤️

Well, friends. It’s time for a change. I gotta move on. This app is no longer serving me as a creator and trying to keep up with it makes me sad and tired and less thrilled about creating. I want to say a huge THANK YOU so much for 10 years of support on here. I wouldn’t be where I am right now without it.
.
Also, just to be clear, I’m NOT deleting this account, or abandoning it completely. I’ll be posting occasionally  about shows, shop updates, new projects, and pushing my Patreon. And obviously to keep in touch with friends. I just can’t keep up with the daily grind. The constant relentless grind of making “content” ::shudders:: to stay relevant in a mystical algorithm, which, most of the time, is completely fruitless and doesn’t give a shit.
.
I want to make good art on my own terms and share it with you when I feel it’s worthy of sharing without being punished with lack of visibility. That being said, since I’ll most likely sink into the muck for lower activity, you can turn on post notifications for me.
.
I’ve made the decision to put all my efforts over on Patreon for exactly all those reasons. And I’d love for you to join me there if you’re able. I know its a big ask. But I will making regular posts and live streams for FREE and will have videos, snail mails stuff, and discounts behind the pay wall. I hope you’ll come join me there.
.
You can find the link to my Patreon in my bio.
.
Thanks again for hearing me out and being here for me. This is really hard. Love you lots. 🖤
.
Daniel Kern
